Crepidochares austrina is a moth in the Eriocottidae family. It was described by Davis in 1990. It is found in Chile.
The length of the forewings is 4.6â€“6 mm for males and 5.8-6.1 mm for females. The forewings are light bronzy brown, with a complex pattern of pale buff to reddish brown and dark fuscous scales. The hindwings are uniform shiny grey. Adults are on wing from the mid-November to mid-December in one generation per year.